Vim Editor Commands for DevOps

These are some of the most commonly used Vim editor commands during DevOps work. Every command below includes what it does and when we use it.

Navigation Commands

G
Moves the cursor to the last line of the file.

gg
Moves the cursor to the first line of the file.

3gg
Moves the cursor to line number 3.

10gg
Moves the cursor to line number 10.

M
Moves the cursor to the middle of the screen.

:4
Moves to line number 4.

:9
Moves to line number 9.

Copy Commands

yy
Copies the current line.

5yy
Copies 5 lines starting from the current line.

Paste Commands

p
Pastes the copied content below the current line.

10p
Pastes the copied content 10 times.

Delete Commands

3dd
Deletes 3 lines.

5dd
Deletes 5 lines.

Undo and Redo Commands

u
Undo the last action.

Ctrl + r
Redo the last undone action.

Search Commands

/folder
Searches forward for the word "folder".

?folder
Searches backward for the word "folder".

n
Moves to next search result.

N
Moves to previous search result.

Replace Commands

:%s/folder/aws
Replaces the first occurrence of "folder" with "aws" in each line.

:%s/folder/aws/g
Replaces all occurrences of "folder" with "aws" in the entire file.

:%s/folder/aws/gc
Replaces with confirmation for each occurrence.

Insert Mode Commands

insert mode
Vim has different modes. Insert mode is used to type text.

i
Enters insert mode before the cursor.

A
Enters insert mode at the end of the line.

I
Enters insert mode at the beginning of the line.

o
Opens a new line below and enters insert mode.

O
Opens a new line above and enters insert mode.

esc
Exits insert mode.

Save and Quit Commands

:w
Saves the file.

:q
Quits the editor.

:q!
Quits without saving changes.

:w!
Forces save.

:wq
Saves and quits.

:wq!
Forces save and quit.

ZZ
Saves and quits (shortcut).

ZQ
Quits without saving (shortcut).

File Open Commands

vim file1
Opens file1 in Vim editor.

vim -o file1 file2
Opens file1 and file2 in horizontal split.

vim -O file1 file2
Opens file1 and file2 in vertical split.

Split Navigation Commands

Ctrl + w w
Switch between split windows.

Ctrl + w h
Move to left split.

Ctrl + w l
Move to right split.

Ctrl + w q
Close current split window.

Visual Mode Commands

v
Starts visual mode.

V
Starts line-wise visual mode.

y
Copies selected text.

d
Deletes selected text.

Additional Useful Commands

:set number
Shows line numbers.

:set nonumber
Hides line numbers.

:set nu
Shortcut to enable line numbers.

:set paste
Enables paste mode.

:set nopaste
Disables paste mode.

Encryption Commands

gpg -c file1
Encrypts file1 with a password.

gpg -d file1
Decrypts file1.

gpg -d file1.gpg
Decrypts encrypted file.
